reviews.text: Quiet at 5.30p Monday. Nice place for coffee after work. Fully seated on Sunday. Few tables.

Starbucks won't give you surprise normally. This one at Exchange square is slightly different. There is a little bar table facing the big open area in the office building. Only a few people pass by in weekend. With my coffee and cake, I feel like enjoying breakfast at home alone. On the other side of the shop, most tables are by the window. You can see the little park facing IFC. In weekdays, no doubt it's extremely busy here. In weekend, it's paradise.
A good place to relax and have a short meeting, no students taking up all the sits. Service is fast and friendly staff.
good atmosphere
Efficient, always available
